Philippines’ 2011 Deficit May Be 2% to 3% of GDP, Purisima Says

-- B y   K a r l   L e s t e r   M .   Y a p
-- 
2011-10-07T12:15:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/philippines-2011-deficit-may-be-2-to-3-of-gdp-purisima-says.html
The  Philippines ’ budget deficit this
year may range from 2 percent to 3 percent of gross domestic
product as the government seeks to bolster spending, Finance
Secretary Cesar Purisima told reporters today in  Manila .  The government prefers a shortfall closer to the cap,
Purisima said. The Philippines may consider pre-funding,
depending on market conditions, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karl Lester M. Yap in Manila at 
 kyap5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Clarissa Batino at 
 cbatino@bloomberg.net  